{"id":"ancient-egypt","files":[{"path":"ATTRIBUTION.md","encoding":"utf8","data":"# Image and research attribution\n\nBook of the Dead of Hunefer (cropped), Wikimedia Commons. Remote image loaded through Wikimedia\nCommons Special:FilePath.\n\nEach lesson uses a distinct remote image and includes a research source link in its notes. The\nremote images are not redistributed in this source package; the reader displays them when connected\nand preserves the local SVG cover offline. Verify current reuse details at each linked Wikimedia\nCommons file page before commercial redistribution.\n\n- **The Nile’s Rhythm** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Nile_River_and_Delta_from_orbit.jpg; research\n  source: https://www.britannica.com/place/Nile-River\n- **A World of Writing** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Rosetta_Stone.JPG; research source:\n  https://www.metmuseum.org/essays/papyrus-in-ancient-egypt\n- **Pharaoh and State** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Colossi_of_Memnon_2017.jpg; research source:\n  https://www.worldhistory.org/Egyptian_Government/\n- **Daily Life and Work** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Model_of_bakery_and_brewery_from_the_tomb_of_Meketre.jpg;\n  research source: https://www.worldhistory.org/article/933/daily-life-in-ancient-egypt/\n- **Preparing for the Afterlife** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Book_of_the_Dead_of_Hunefer_cropped_1.jpg;\n  research source: https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/557590\n- **How Egypt Is Remembered** — image:\n  https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:FilePath/Temple_of_Hatshepsut_2010.jpg; research\n  source: https://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/egyp/hd_egyp.htm\n"},{"path":"assets/images/cover.svg","encoding":"utf8","data":"<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" viewBox=\"0 0 1600 900\"><rect width=\"1600\" height=\